social_posts.post_text: I have chosen to live the life I am living. Because every action, every thought and every emotion is a choice. A choice toward freedom rather than fear.

A full moon in the sign of Gemini. After dinner last night, as I was walking through Soho, I looked up and was so in awe of how beautiful and luminous this moon was. She always reminds me that my light can shine the brightest even in my darkest moments. That as the clouds of my life pass through, there will be clarity revealed. I hope you are all having a blessed December my loves 💌🌚🌝

I am thinking a lot about how and the way I wish to move within this world. It’s been a lot of reflecting these past few weeks for me. Life continues to evolve, whether we like it or not. And thus, I along with it. More than simply doing and simply being. I wish to merge the two. Where it is the doing that feeds my being and the being that feeds my doing.
Today marks one month living in New York. Just been a lot of eating, art and walking. My favorite activities 🥰🥰🥰🥰
Sometimes you just need a warm unagi and rice meal to cure the winter blues. Also I’m trying to learn how to dress for winter 🫠🥶🤍🤍🤍

It's the beginning of a new season, a winter melody. Welcoming it in with Issey Miyake's L'Eau d'Issey. Its fresh aquatic fragrance reminds me of the moments after rainfall. My perfect holiday gift for my childhood best friend, who is a nature lover. @isseymiyakeparfums #isseymiyakeparfums #partner

I am slowly discovering where my heart belongs. Getting to this space wasn’t easy, but it was simple. The simple decision of shedding the excess, shedding all that no longer belongs to me, to my heart. And moving in the direction that brought me the light. The light that is within myself. 💌

I always look forward to winter. The time when we embrace the darkness, within and without. As we once did in our mother’s womb, allow creation to bloom quietly and softly. 

Today is winter solstice, the shortest day and longest night of the year. A time to rest and go within. I love to dive deep into my feminine yin at this time. For me, it is so healing and nourishing. A warmth that burns eternally inside of me.
I followed my heart, and it led me here 🫀
New York coziness 🤍😌

Another year of blessings coming to a close. Thank you to each and every one of you who continue to follow my journey here. Wishing you all the most wonderful and warmest holidays. Love, Fong 🤍🤍🤍🤍🎄❄️🥰

The biggest lesson that I have learned this past year from navigating through the different spaces in my life, is remaining in my INTEGRITY. We live in a world of constant distraction and peer pressure that so easily takes us away from our inner center. Sometimes, we will lose sight of ourselves because of the shiny things dangling in front of us. But, at the end of the day, when we become still and see with our hearts, not our eyes, our visions will become crystal clear.
My morning ritual. I love making my morning matcha and setting my intentions for the day. And on days when I’m not in a good mood, I’ll sometimes shout the intentions out loud lol 😌🍵

Reflecting upon this past year, I have deep gratitude for how much I have committed to stepping outside of my comfort zone. I have always enjoyed taking risks, because as they say, the greater the risk, the greater the reward ;) and I have never been one to stay complacent.

However you choose to lead your life, I hope that it is a life that excites you, brings you passion and gives you fulfillment. As the inspiring Viktor Frankl once said, “Those who have a ‘why’ to live, can bear almost any ‘how’.

I have learned the art of dying. To bring death upon the women who had once lived within me. And it is their deaths that give birth to the woman I am today. As one cannot truly live unless one is intimate with death. I must change in form if I desire to grow and to outgrow who I once was. Because who I am tomorrow will no longer be who I am today. And it is foolish to think that who you were yesterday can claim the gifts that belong to who you are tomorrow. 🫀🥀

I believe that change can be activated on any given day. That one can choose to start a new path in life in just a matter of a second's decision. Whatever change may mean for you, know that it is the one constant in life we can find solace in.

Life is made up of choices and decisions. And while my human ego often tries to interfere, I do the work to allow my heart and soul to lead. So that I can cultivate a conditioning for change. And to keep this life of mine open to possibilities beyond me.

Because when nothing is certain, anything is possible.

It is finally here. My first collection of poetry titled: Through The Veins Of My Heart. To be honest, I never thought I would publish poetry. As a young teen, I enjoyed writing song lyrics as I once had a dream to be a songwriter. To me, writing songs and poetry overlap and I truly find so much joy expressing myself through this medium.

This is my first self-published project and I am so excited to share it with you. It has been a fun learning process and I am looking forward to learning more along the way.

This collection of poetry is for the sensitive dreamers and lovers who yearn to be seen and heard, but most of all, understood.

social_posts.post_text:
“Life shrinks or expands in proportion to one’s courage.” - #AnaïsNin

Indeed, it is true.

Fear is a normal emotion we all feel. It is always there, nothing special. The beautiful alchemy occurs when we pour in courage and allow it to seep in to overcome the fear. That is when transformation truly begins.

I believe that change can be activated on any given day. That one can choose to start a new path in life in just a matter of a second's decision. Change is respected and change is feared. Whatever change may mean for you, know that it is the one constant in life we can find solace in.

Life is made up of choices and decisions. And while my human ego often tries to interfere, I do the work to allow my heart and soul to lead. So that I can cultivate a conditioning for change. And to keep this life of mine open to possibilities beyond me.

Because when nothing is certain, anything is possible.

We have a full moon upon us this Sunday 2/5. A reminder to set your intentions this weekend, because what you focus on is what grows. Feel into your heart, feel into your body. This is the time for self expansion, this is the time for truly living. For the power within is what is real and is what is true. To this day, I have manifested everything that is my life. Channeling the energies of the universe and its beautiful powers and having faith in the unseen is the secret. Do you dare to dream a bigger dream? 🤍🌝
Finally feeling alive again. Health is wealth. 💓💓💓

Taking moments to pause to shed the excess for clarity. Because it is no longer about continuously adding to who I think I should be, but rather to take away who I no longer am and never was. And as we embark on a new moon in Pisces this time of year, I wish you the courage to be who you truly are 🤍

Do you ever ask questions to your future self? I did and I still do. I remember how just 5-6 years ago, I was not the version of myself that I loved and adored. I knew I had a lot of work to do - the inner work - on myself. I became obsessed. Obsessed with becoming the brightest version of me that I’d wake up to every morning smiling to. I wanted to grow in love with myself.

We are all seeking something in this life. And often, most people do not realize that the reason they keep plateauing and hitting walls in their growth is not because they haven’t found the right answers, it is because they are not asking the right questions that serve them best. Because in order to have true clarity in the direction you most deeply resonate with, you must be willing to pinpoint what exactly is necessary and unnecessary.

And with that, I’d like to leave these questions for you: What experiences do you want to have in the next 6 months, 12 months? And who do you need to become to achieve those experiences?

Do not underestimate what you can do in one year once you get clear on what you want to achieve and who you need to be ❤️

social_posts.post_text:
We don’t see things as they are, we see them as we are. #AnaisNin

Life is a continuous reflection of how you see yourself, how you carry yourself and what you believe you deserve. Understanding this concept changed my entire life. Because I realized that it was no longer the things and people outside of me that determined how I experience my life. Rather it is about everything I experience within myself that determines my life experiences.

Every day I am learning and discovering more about the woman I am and the woman I desire to be. We all have two lives. The second one begins when you realize you only have one. I’m not wasting any more time. As for yourself, that is for you to decide. What are you going to do? 🌸🌸🌸

After a few months of a much needed rest, I am finally ready to begin the next chapter of my story. My studio is slowly coming together and I am so excited to get back to painting again. My dream of creating my own little universe is taking shape. My visions are becoming more clear. My thoughts and ideas have gained more clarity.

I have learned that unless I consciously work to take control of my environment to support the person I desire to be - my environment, left alone, would simply create me as it pleases. And that is not the life I desire to lead. 

I am very much looking forward to sharing with you this next beginning my loves. Thank you for being here ❤️

Today marks the beginning of the last year of my 20s. Age has always been a fascinating concept to me. I guess it is because it is tied to the concept of time which I am also so intrigued by.

I remember the first years of entering my 20s. It was a rough start. But those were the moments that prepared me for my becoming and I would not change a thing. I remember so vividly the moments of falling to rock bottom and picking myself up, time and time again.

My late twenties have been about seeking clarity and finding my truth. And I can tell you that today I am feeling the most alive I have ever felt. I am grateful for my younger self for taking the risks that have led me to where I am today. I most definitely will not let her efforts go to waste ❤️

I must also thank you, my beautiful community on here. For being by my side throughout these many years. For giving me the opportunity to live the life of my dreams. You are all a part of my path 🫶🏻💌

I’d like to leave you this poem from page 39 of Through The Veins Of My Heart 🫀 it represents what I feel most deeply.
I must go where I feel most alive. Page 58 from Through The Veins Of My Heart 🫀

social_posts.post_text: “I just have three things to teach: simplicity, patience, compassion.” #LaoZi

Exactly one year ago, around the time of my birthday, I was in a place completely different than where I am today. Mentally, emotionally and physically.

I love this statement quote by Alain de Botton, “Anyone who isn’t embarrassed of who they were last year probably isn’t learning enough.”

When I look back at the person I was one year ago, if I were still navigating through life today the same way she did, I would definitely be a little bit embarrassed. And this is not to say that I am ashamed of who I was, absolutely not. It is simply to place emphasis on the amount of growth that has taken place. The qualitative internal changes that have transformed me as an individual.

I have never been more excited for life. Because I know and understand that I am creating all that I am experiencing. 🎂🫀🌸
Little moments of sweetness 🥀🥀🥀🥀

All my life growing up, I had felt an immense discomfort in my own skin. From all the societal conditioning and expectations, it was difficult to have the correct discernment as an impressionable young child. I did not understand nor know how to express myself in a way that felt safe to me. I deeply yearned to be free. And as a young adult, this desire led me to discover myself for the first time.

Understanding that life is a continuous and ever-evolving journey helped me to learn to love myself regardless of where I am, what I am and who I am. I learned to become the love I never received. It is an effort each and every day as it is a practice. A practice that continues to evolve with time. 🫀🥀

Photos @shintani

social_posts.post_text:
“The more I read, the more I acquire, the more certain I am that I know nothing.” #Voltaire

I periodically go back to this quote. To quiet my mind and to humble my ego. While I believe we are all both teacher and student, I find the most joy being the student. Always.

“Good things take time, great things take a little longer.” To my young, impatient and impulsive self, hearing those words would usually be followed by an exasperated sigh and mental resistance.

Now, being in my late twenties and truly understanding the gift of compound interest, I see the beauty of experiencing life through the lens of a marathon rather than a sprint.

Learning how to be patient and practicing deliberately slowing down is changing how I am experiencing my day to day. No longer am I overwhelmed by anxiety and guilt of not always being “productive” and “busy” in this results driven society. I have also shifted my definitions of what those two words mean.

I am still learning how to become my most optimized self. But I am doing so in a way that supports my well-being by lessening the comparisons to external metrics and rather focusing on how I have improved from who I was yesterday. 🫀🌸

Over time, I have found that inner peace is not something outside ourselves, an unreachable goal that we keep chasing. Instead, it is a state of being, it is the true core of our inner being. It is our natural state when we slough off the anxiety, the worries, the fear, the what ifs, when we break down the barriers and blockages we have unconsciously built as a result of being confronted with life’s challenges. We do it out of self-defense, out of habit, and many other reasons. But in spite of this, it is important to remember our true core lies in a state of peacefulness.

Photo @shintani

The female body is constantly under scrutiny and has been the center of many conversations and controversy for centuries. Learning to love and to embrace my body was my own rebellion against the society that tells us we are not enough. To be born a woman, was the greatest gift I was given. Discovering my curves and edges will be my lifelong lesson. @cuup #supportedbycuup

I have loved and I have let go of that love, yet I am loving again. When you first let go, you feel as though you have lost a part of yourself. The truth is, love never leaves, it simply waits for you to return. Like a small flame that burns eternally in your heart, it cannot die. This time, I have returned. I am loving me, the one I needed to give it to the most. Have you returned?

Entering into a new season of my life. A season that involves expanding into the version of me I have always desired to be. This means growing through the discomforts as well as the joys. Because one cannot have pleasure without pain. It is the contrasts that give me the perspectives to truly cherish what it is I have. And I could not be more grateful. Some days are hard, where merely placing one foot in front of the other and taking that one step is the biggest accomplishment of the day. And some days, I feel as though I’ve just run a marathon and crossing the finish line makes me feel like I am in heaven. Regardless, both involve progress and that is all that matters. It is what is important. That I have improved from where I was and who I was yesterday. 🫀🫀🫀

I am thinking a lot about how and the way I wish to move within this world. It has been a time of reflection these past few weeks for me. Life continues to evolve, whether we like it or not. And thus, I along with it. More than simply doing and simply being. I wish to merge the two. Where it is the doing that feeds my being and the being that feeds my doing. At the end of the day, all that matters is what is the truth of my heart. The truth, stripped from the projections and perceptions that have been layered upon me since my birth. The truth, in its purity and simplicity. And so I allow myself to be reborn from the ashes of what and who I once was.

social_posts.post_text: I have spent my entire life searching and seeking for something. What it was, I did not know. But, I do know now. The cultivation of love and inner peace that lives within my heart and soul. That is what matters, that is what is true. Everything else, will eventually fade away. And once again, you will only be left with your self.

What it means to be a woman, I am still discovering and unearthing. Finding pleasure in my own tenderness, my vulnerability. It is the sweet syrup of my soul. I have unveiled a joy buried deep in my heart.  And now, I will let it bloom. Because at last, I can no longer be silenced and suppressed. Will you join me, darlings?

Painting is my meditation and medicine. It is where I go to pour out my soul and to bare my heart. To be able to share this with you, is the greatest blessing of my life.

Stillness, 2023

The most important thing I prioritize is my inner peace. After years of suffering from anxiety that stemmed from childhood trauma and spending several more years focusing on healing and growing, inner peace has become my north star.

The question I always ask myself when I make a decision is: does this bring me closer to my inner peace or does it take me further away?

I have realized that nothing and no one is worth sacrificing my mental health for. Because one cannot put a price tag on the deep feeling of being in harmony with oneself.

What does inner peace mean to you?

(Postcards from Japan because I’ve been busy painting🌸)

Growth and change is an ever-evolving process; there is an ebb and flow to it. Some months I find myself deep in the abyss peeling back layers and layers of deeply rooted trauma. Some months I find myself basking in the light, my own light. Light that seeped through the cracks of a once broken soul. Each time when I think I know myself, I am once again humbled by what I did not know. Then the process begins again. A process that has become more friend than foe.

(Postcards from Japan 🌸)

We all have our own individual stories and each of us lead lives as complex and unique as the other. That is the beauty of being a human.

The most important thing I have learned personally is that faith is my fortune. To always believe in the unseen and that no matter that, I do have the power within to create the life I desire and to walk a path of my own choosing.

Because I have realized that it is the possibility of having a dream come true that makes life worth living. Every single day is a blessing. ❤️‍🔥

(Postcards from Japan 🌸)

My childhood dream come true! Attending my very first Chanel fashion show. Aside from art, fashion had always been one of my greatest fascinations and adorations. I simply love styling and the art of a beautiful silhouette and color palette. All the drama, sophistication and elegance. I have always been obsessed.

To my 15 year old self who founded my high school’s first fashion club and never stopped sharing her love for fashion / style - keep going darling, you are absolutely on the right path 🥰🤍

Thank you @chanelofficial for this beautiful experience. And to have it here in Los Angeles, the city I moved to at age 18 with big dreams and not knowing anyone or anything. After having lived here for 10 years, I feel it has finally come full circle. I still love fashion and I still have big dreams. #ChanelCruise

I have chosen to live the life I am living. Because every action, every thought and every emotion is a choice. A choice toward freedom rather than fear. I have chosen to love myself for who I am, rather than for what I am doing. Because it is my being that fuels my doing.

To create a life story founded upon a deep love for experiencing, rather than simply existing. This is what love means to me. This is what makes my heart pound ferociously. This is what I live for. 🫀

Everything is meaningless until you give it meaning. But, it must be of wisdom from your deepest soul experience. Otherwise, it is only borrowed knowledge. And that is no different than being ignorant. 🌸🌸🌸

I can hardly believe that I have been living in New York City for half a year now. It has been one of the best decisions of my life. I have always been one to completely uproot my surroundings when I needed to expand. When I felt that deep gut feeling of desire to move last year, I knew that New York would be my destination.

I have spent the past few weeks setting up my new art studio space. It has been a literal dream unfolding. It has been nearly five years now since I’ve begun my journey as a fine artist. I have learned so much within these few years. Not only about how I wish to navigate my craft, but most importantly, my values and principles as a creative.

I am excited to share more with you soon! In the meantime, thank you for being here ❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥

Slow progress is still progress. And that is what I have been leaning into these last few months, rather than criticizing myself for not making things happen quickly enough. I came to think, according to whose timeline?

It’s understandable given that we live within such a fast paced digital era, that if we feel we are not “keeping up”, then perhaps we may be left behind.

For many years, I’ve had this fear in the back of my mind. Yet, I knew it was not a sustainable approach to life for me. It was not the way of life I desired. I wanted to create and live according to my own terms.

So I started to shift my mindset. And that was the game changer for me. Because it changed my perspective on what creating and what life meant to me. I am here to tell you that slow progress is still progress and that is to be celebrated as well ❤️

One of the most important lessons in life I have learned thus far is that while we can be uncertain about many things in life, we must absolutely not be uncertain about who we are and what it is we desire.

Because life is a mirror and when we are uncertain about who we are and what it is we desire, then that is the visceral experience we will live through.

Lesson number one: learning who I truly am, what I truly value (not what I think I value based on what I am exposed to) and developing well informed discernment.

Lesson number two: discovering what it is I desire and making the decisions that it is available to me. That I am enough and worthy of it simply because I desire it.

And that, is how you change your life my darlings ❤️ Now let me ask you, what do you desire in this life?

When reflections are made and awareness is raised, changes will soon follow. It is so important to understand yourself. To truly know yourself from within. It is only then that you can move forward in your life with a purpose, with intention and with a goal in mind. To know yourself is to know what to seek. Whatever that may be… ❤️

But why not? Why not choose to believe in your own magic, rather than to suppress all the gifts you have to offer to this earthly experience? You do not need to wait for permission to be. And if you must have it, then here it is. This is your permission slip.

Do you dare to take a chance, on yourself, for yourself?

I dare you, darling.

Finding my zen in Kyoto. I love this discreet little temple just down the street from the famous Tofuku-ji temple. I have always loved round windows / openings that are present in a lot of Asian architecture. In Japanese architecture, round windows also symbolize the concept of “mitate”. Mitate means to repurpose, “to look again.” Essentially to enable an object to be perceived in a new way, to contemplate it as if it was something else. Thus, round windows can be seen as an extension of nature, something outside the building which emits natural light, such the sun and the moon.

1st temple: 芬陀院（雪舟寺)
2nd temple shown: #kenninji Temple

I believe that change can be activated on any given day. That one can choose to start a new path in life in just a matter of a second’s decision. Change is revered and change is feared. Whatever change may mean for you, know that it is the one constant in life that we can find solace in.

The unknown is scary. It is human nature to want to be safe and to know what will happen next. We are so conditioned that we can be in great discomfort in the state of not knowing what to do. But I do not want to lead a life of predictability, rather, I want to create my own. I yearn to be free. And in order to be free, one must learn to embrace the unknown and find beauty in uncertainty.

To shape this kind of life experience, one must be willing to cultivate the self-discipline for the self-preservation of one’s authenticity. To not continue to be stained by society’s temptations and be caged by the illusion of restrictions.

Life is made up of choices and decisions. And while my human ego often tries to interfere, I do the work to allow my heart and soul lead. So that I can cultivate a conditioning for change. And to keep this life of mine open to possibilities beyond me.

I knew I had a lot of work to do - the inner work - on myself. I became obsessed. Obsessed with becoming the brightest version of me that I’d wake up to every morning smiling to. I wanted to grow in love with myself.

We are all seeking something in this life. And often, most people do not realize that the reason they keep plateauing and hitting walls in their growth is not because they haven’t found the right answers, it is because they are not asking the right questions that serve them best. Because in order to have true clarity in the direction you most deeply resonate with, you must be willing to pinpoint what exactly is necessary and unnecessary.

And with that, I’d like to leave these questions for you: What experiences do you want to have in the next 6 months, 12 months? And who do you need to become to achieve those experiences?

Do not underestimate what you can do in one year once you get clear on what you want to achieve and who you need to be 🫀

Tea ceremony lesson with sensei @hoshimado121111 🍵🤍

One passion of mine is to learn the art of a Traditional Japanese Tea Ceremony. Much of its history and origin comes from ancient China and thus, I feel a sense of belonging and connection. This practice takes dedication and patience. I had my first lesson in 2019 with Sensei @hoshimado121111 and I absolutely fell in love with it. Since then, I do my best to take a lesson each time I travel back to Japan. The teachings of these lessons embody so much of the principles that I hold close to my heart. Stillness, thoughtfulness, purity, patience, community and spirituality.

My intention for 2024 is to continue to make time for the things that are, while not urgent, are important to me. I no longer want to say “one day, I will…” I have decided that the vision I want for my future is the vision I will have today. And so it is.
